ry (b. [[1799]]) (assassinated)\n* [[February 3]] &ndash; [[Marie Duplessis]], French courtesan (b. [[1824]])\n* [[March 9]] &ndash; [[Mary Anning]], British paleontologist (b. [[1799]])\n* [[April 21]] &ndash; [[Barbara Spooner Wilberforce]], wife of British abolitionist William Wilberforce (b. [[1777]])\n* [[April 30]] &ndash; [[Archduke Charles, Duke of Teschen|Archduke Charles of Austria]], Austrian general (b. [[1771]])\n* [[May 14]] &ndash; [[Fanny Mendelssohn]], German composer, pianist (b. [[1805]])\n* [[May 15]] &ndash; [[Daniel O'Connell]], Irish politician who promoted the [[Roman Catholic Relief Act 1829]] (b. [[1775]])\n* [[May 16]] &ndash; [[Vicente Rocafuerte]], 2nd President of Ecuador (b. [[1783]])\n* [[May 29]] &ndash; [[Emmanuel de Grouchy, Marquis de Grouchy]], French marshal (b. [[1766]])\n* [[May 31]] &ndash; [[Abbasgulu Bakikhanov]], Azerbaijani writer (b. [[1794]])\n* [[June 11]] &ndash; [[John Franklin|Sir John Franklin]], British explorer (b. [[1786]])\n\n=== July&ndash;December ===\n[[File:Mendelssohn Bartholdy.jpg|thumb|110px|right|110px|[[Felix Mendelssohn]]]]\n* [[July 7]] &ndash; [[Thomas Carpenter (glassmaker)|Thomas Carpenter]], American glassmaker (b. [[1752]])\n* [[July 16]] &ndash; [[Karl Friedrich Burdach]], German physiologist (b. [[1776]])\n* [[September 4]] &ndash; [[Franti\u0161ek Vladislav Hek]], Czech patriot (b. [[1769]])\n* [[September 13]] &ndash; [[Nicolas Oudinot]], French marshal (b. [[1767]])\n* [[October 3]] &ndash; [[Charles Hatchett]], English chemist (b. [[1765]])\n* [[October 22]] \n** [[Henriette Herz]], German salonni\u00e9re (b. [[1764]])\n** Negus [[Sahle Selassie]] of [[Shewa]] (b. c. [[1795]])\n* [[November 4]] &ndash; [[Felix Mendelssohn]], German composer (b. [[1809]])\n* [[December 14]]\n** [[Manuel Jos\u00e9 Arce]], Central American politician (b. [[1787]])\n** [[Dorothy Ann Thrupp]], British psalmist (b. [[1779]])\n* Unknown: [[Jeanne Genevi\u00e8ve Labrosse]], French balloonist and parachutist (b. [[